summary: This is a brief email exchange between FBI agents in New York and Paris, initiated by a new agent in Paris seeking to 'touch base' regarding the Epstein case. It indicates ongoing FBI coordination on the investigation across international offices.
keyFacts: An FBI agent newly stationed in Paris reached out to an FBI agent in New York to coordinate on the Epstein case on September 13, 2019.
The communication indicates active, international FBI involvement in the Epstein investigation.
The document is a routine internal email, showing operational coordination rather than containing specific investigative details.
